com.ibm.team.scm.common

Interface IBaseline

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IAuditable, IAuditableHandle, IBaselineHandle, IContextHandle, IItem, IItemHandle, IManagedItem, IManagedItemHandle

    public interface IBaseline
extends IBaselineHandle, IAuditable
    A Baseline represents an immutable Configuration of a set of Versionables (i.e. it records the StateId of a subset of the Versionables in a Repository), and the history of ChangeSets which led up to the Configuration.

    Notes:

    • All interesting protocol for working with Baselines is available via IWorkspaceConnection and IBaselineConnection.
    • The protocol exposed here is for examining the attributes of a Baseline that are not related to the Configuration itself; for example, the audit history, and the related component.
    • Clients cannot create baseline auditables in the normal fashion. Creating baselines can only be done with special methods on IWorkspaceConnection, and IWorkspaceManager.
    • This auditable has additional properties that are not exposed to clients.

    Feature access profile values:

    • id: SMALL
    • name: SMALL
    • comment: DEFAULT
    • component: DEFAULT

    Since:
    0.5
